name: Chapter 1
note:
<SG:Nice to meet you, everyone. For those who are already familiar, it's been a while. I will
be in charge of the summary. Please take care of me. Now, you are heading towards the
eradication of thieves. First, let's go north and head to the thieves' cave.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2
note:
<SG:It seems we have arrived at the thief's cave. There are thieves here who have made this
their stronghold, let's defeat their leader. By the way, even if we lose now, there will
be no consequences. Let's proceed quietly.>           // (1)
<SG:>//

name: Chapter 2
note:
<SG:It seems we have arrived at the thief's cave. There are thieves here who have made this
their stronghold, let's defeat their leader. By the way, even if we lose now, there will
be no consequences. Let's proceed quietly.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Behind the scenes
note:
<SG:Congratulations on clearing the game. I'm glad you played until the ending. So, let's go
behind the scenes. Basically, it's the same as the intermission. However, if you talk to
the beautiful receptionist, you can see an ending that meets certain conditions. Hmph, as
expected of me. A perfect introduction. My role ends here. Thank you for your company. I
hope we can meet again. Well, you can meet a very beautiful receptionist, though.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 12
note:
<SG:The appearance of the walls and ground has changed. This must mean that the core is
getting closer. If we've come this far, I think we're almost there. However, the monsters
have also become stronger, so let's proceed without letting our guard down.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 11
note:
<SG:We have entered the Earth Beast. We must proceed towards the core no matter what. I
believe the core is located towards the center of the Earth Beast. However, it just looks
like a normal mountain. It's still unclear whether it's because it has just awakened or if
it will remain as a mountain even after awakening.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 10
note:
<SG:Well, this will be the last greeting. So let me say it. Thank you for your support. Now,
let's head towards the Earth Beast. Leave the town and go north. It's to the east of the
Temple of the Earth. Once you enter the Earth Beast, there's no way to escape and there
are no recovery points. I think it's best to prepare thoroughly. You might find some good
equipment being sold as well.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Final Chapter 9
note:
<SG:Thank goodness, we found a breakthrough. But how did you, [Conductor]-sama, figure it out?
There are some long-lived races, so there might be a source of information... But it's not
something to think about right now. Let's just go to the cafeteria for now.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Final Chapter 8
note:
<SG:Urgent: How to defeat a monster that regenerates based on the size of the mountain. As
expected, we couldn't even find a breakthrough. In the first place, there is little
information about the Earth Beast because it takes a long time for them to revive. The
last time an Earth Beast appeared was over 100 years ago. The lack of information is one
of the problems. For now, let's have a chat with everyone to change the mood.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 7
note:
<SG:Congratulations on awakening, Lady Prae. However, it seems that a problem has also arisen.
Due to your hasty actions, the Earth Beast has been revived. Let's return to the base to
come up with a countermeasure. I wonder if we can somehow deal with such a formidable
opponent.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 6
note:
<SG:Alright, let's go, let's go. Let's aim for the back. If you want to recover, please come
back. It's been a long journey so far, so we should find it soon. Let's proceed
efficiently.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 5
note:
<SG:It's quite a long journey, isn't it? Let's take a break for now. Since it's called a
temple, I suppose people used to live here. I'm curious about this place being too
beautiful. Anyway, let's see how everyone is doing for now.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4
note:
<SG:It's a dilapidated temple, isn't it? Since no one lives here, it hasn't been maintained.
Anyway, let's proceed further. Although we call it an investigation, our goal is to find
the succubus we encountered before.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3
note:
<SG:It became an investigation of the Earth Temple as originally planned. Once you're
prepared, leave the town and head north. It's strange to rely on someone (a succubus)
whose background is unknown, but I guess they're just that desperate. There's no other
choice, after all.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2
note:
<SG: It's become quite a problem, hasn't it? Although I wasn't feeling well, I suddenly fell
into a coma. I can't figure out what to do in such a sudden situation. For now, let's go
back to the base and have a discussion. By the way, the beautiful receptionist isn't here
today. She only works once a week!>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 1
note:
<SG:This marks the beginning of the final chapter. Our objective this time is to investigate
the Temple of the Earth. For now, let's just spend today leisurely since we'll be heading
out tomorrow. By the way, the Earth Beasts are one of the Four Demon Beasts known on this
continent. Even if you defeat them, they will revive after a certain amount of time and
are said to be immortal beasts. It is said that using a sealing technique after defeating
them can delay their revival, but the truth behind it remains a mystery.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Outer Chapter
note:
<SG:Yes, it's Gai Shou. I'm not sure if the meaning is correct. This time, what we're going to
do is search for the Conductor. There won't be any explanations about the location or
anything this time. I apologize. Looks like I ended up with the unfortunate ones. I hope
things go well.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Intermission 4
note:
<SG:It's intermission. I'll give the same explanation as before. Let's complete dispatch
quests to increase our reputation. When our reputation is high enough, we can receive main
quests from the receptionist. Accepting a main quest will start the next chapter. However,
you were approached by a suspicious man, right? If you're curious, why not talk to him?
Speaking of which, managing your save data is important. If you happen to talk to someone
and make a choice, it might lock you into a certain route and you won't be able to go
back. If you plan on talking to the suspicious person, it might be a good idea to save
beforehand.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Verse 17
note:
<SG:Yuube was having fun. It's a problem that this greeting is used so often, we need to think
of something. Now, it's time for another dungeon conquest. Let's go with enthusiasm. In my
prediction, the end point is coming soon. Let's rush through it all at once.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Scene 16
note:
<SG:You've returned to the town again. It's understandable that it's a big burden on your
body. Please do your best tonight too. Oh, you can't go outside today.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Scene 15
note:
<SG:This time it was a worm as the opponent, huh? It's a shame that it was buried in the
ground and couldn't be seen. Since Nonna-sama is in a bad situation, let's return to the
town. We should be able to go back if we proceed.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Scene 14
note:
<SG:Now it's tentacles, huh? It's a shame that we can't proceed if we help now. Let's move
forward in order to help. Although they seem to be enjoying it in their own way, it looks
like they've been subjected to physical modifications in the dungeon.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Section 13
note:
<SG:Good morning. Last night was enjoyable, wasn't it? Yes, let's leave that topic here. Now,
let's resume our dungeon exploration. I wonder what challenges await us next. Let's have
fun!>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Part 12
note:
<SG:I have returned once again, at the gate. It is also called the front of the city. It's not
in the middle of town, you know. Now, let's go and see how everyone is doing. There is one
person in the annex of the inn, two people in the main building, one person outside, and
one person in the warehouse. Once we have finished checking on everyone, let's return to
Lady Saria's place in the annex.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4-11
note:
<SG:A spirit... a lewd spirit, perhaps? Why would it be here of all places? If someone is
managing it, could it be a succubus spirit? There's no point in pondering things we don't
know. I do think it was easier compared to the previous task. Though Fross-sama might be
an exception. For now, let's continue as is. I believe it would be troublesome if we were
to go back here.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Level 10
note:
<SG:Hmmm, I see... It's a strange device. It must be for obtaining magical power. It seems to
be connected to the dungeon. If it's left alone like this, Fross-sama will also suffer.
Let's quickly proceed and set it free. By the way, this dungeon is alive. Whether it has a
will or not is a mystery.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Verse 9
note:
<SG:Everyone seems to be in good health, which is a relief. Let's resume our dungeon
exploration. I wonder what challenges await us next. Sigh... If only we could assign
someone else to do the explanations, it would make things easier...>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, 8
note:
<SG:Last night was enjoyable, wasn't it? (smirk) It seems like everyone had a good time. I'm
glad to see everyone looking well. Shall I go check on everyone's condition again? It
wouldn't be wise to explore the dungeon while feeling unwell. As for their whereabouts,
there are two people in the annex of the inn, one person in the main building, one person
outside, and one person in the warehouse.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Verse 7
note:
<SG:  It seems you're feeling down. I wonder if this is something that would make you happy if
you're into NTR. If that's the case, then congratulations, I suppose. Well, either way is
fine. Judging from Kuno-sama's demeanor, it seems other women are also worried. Let's go
check on them. They should be outside in pairs, one in the inn, one in the tent, and one
in the warehouse. In this case, the inn refers to the main building with a sign, not the
separate building where they are staying.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Section 6
note:
<SG:Ah, yes, thank you for your hard work. Well then, I'll be going now... Oh, is that not
allowed? Shall we talk about magical tools? When it comes to magical tools that can create
dungeons, there doesn't seem to be anyone on the surface who can make them at the moment.
I don't know about the demon world or the heavenly realm though. So they must either be
something that has been passed down since ancient times or something brought from the
demon world or heavenly realm. Shall we continue forward then? It would be troublesome to
go back, so please proceed.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4, Section 5
note:
<SG:I see, it's an erotic dungeon. Since I'm not in charge of anything erotic, it's difficult
for me to explain. It's quite troublesome. Anyway, let's move forward to help Shia-sama
and the others. We just need magic temporarily to proceed. Once we move forward, there
won't be any problems.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4
note:
<SG: It's my condolences. That was quite an embarrassing play, wasn't it? If you're not
mentally strong, it could cause problems in your future life. Now, let's start the dungeon
conquest. I'm excited to see what kind of traps there are. Huh? You don't seem excited
because I'm reading it in a monotone voice? Please don't mind that. Let's do our best and
move forward.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4-3
note:
<SG:It's definitely an erotic dungeon, isn't it? The gimmicks are very disappointing. But
there's no point in complaining about it. Let's head towards the promotion. Taro-sama,
your responsibility is the inn and the tavern. It's inside the orange-colored building to
the northwest. After the promotion is over, please come back and talk to Kuno-sama.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4-2
note:
<SG:Well, it's terrible, isn't it? To steal someone's newlywed. Are you okay as a person? Just
kidding. I believe love is freedom. I think even love affairs are fine, of course. There
are no rules like first come, first served. Now, let's head towards dungeon conquest. If
it's Saria-sama, she is in the same place as yesterday, to the south of the gate.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 4-1
note:
<SG:Chapter 4 has begun. It seems we have already arrived at our destination. However... an
Erotic Dungeon? The name is quite direct, and I don't want to get involved. It might be
just right for the succubi though. For now, let's return to report. Lady Saria, the female
knight, is located to the south of the gate. A little information: we are currently in
front of the gate of the city of Longe. It's a fairly large city and there is an entrance
fee. That's why there are cheap inns set up in front of the gate. Taro-sama and the others
are also using those inns.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Intermission 3-2
note:
<SG:  It's intermission. I'll explain the same thing as before. Let's complete dispatch quests
to increase our reputation. When our reputation is high, we can receive main quests from
the receptionist. Starting a main quest will begin the next chapter. The demon race has a
huge difference in their bodies. They don't resemble Homo sapiens at all. That's why it's
difficult to treat Lady Prae. It's because they can sustain themselves with magical power,
even without internal organs, and unnecessary things don't remain in their bodies.
Originally, Lady Prae can eat normally as well.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Intermission 3-1
note:
<SG:Oh, it must be tough just coming back. There hasn't been any news from the Water Temple
either. Well then, let's go look for a very beautiful receptionist. Why don't you try
going outside the room for now?>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Verse 24
note:
<SG:Oh, Uka-sama has changed again. Let's investigate the situation on the island. Once we're
done looking around, let's talk to Dalton-sama. You're quite active, aren't you?>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Verse 23
note:
<SG:We have arrived at Klein Island. It's peaceful outside. Let's dive into the cave in the
center of the island and head deeper. There seems to be a strong monster there. Once we
defeat it, let's exit the cave.   Petit Information Corner: Monsters are born from magic
power and also reproduce. They mainly originate from areas with high magic concentration,
but the exact principles are not understood. Additionally, they seem to prefer places with
high magic concentration.   By the way, this is why the town cannot be too large. If it
becomes too big, the population increases and the magic concentration rises, causing
monsters to appear in the town as well.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Verse 22
note:
<SG:Good morning, it's a nice morning, isn't it? It seems like the future plans have been
decided. Let's go to the port and talk to the captain again. We can go to the nearby
island (Klein Island). There might be battles on the island, so let's make sure we're well
prepared.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Verse 21
note:
<SG:I'm glad we were able to return safely. As for what happened at the temple, no comment.
Shall we return to the inn for today? Lady Shia should have returned ahead of us.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Page 20
note:
<SG:It seems they came to pick us up with the repaired ship. Let's head to the temple in the
north. Huh? You're asking why Kuno-sama is feeling better? Well... I wonder what happened
exactly? While the ship was being repaired, it seems Rodrigo-sama took Kuno-sama to his
room and did something...>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Section 19
note:
<SG:It seems like something has happened. Let's go investigate the northern gate. By
protecting a worried woman, love might be born, you know.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Section 18
note:
<SG:Taro-sama, you have returned. It seems that while Shia-sama was asleep, she was
investigating the inside. It appears that there was nothing. Since she is awake, let's
talk to Shia-sama. We don't know what will happen.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Scene 17
note:
<SG:You were able to enter the Raulus Forest, right? Now all that's left is to go and get the
Fross Fruit and come back. It doesn't seem to be near the entrance, so let's head deeper
into the forest.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Scene 16
note:
<SG:The road was closed. And it was done by a famous conductor. However, it seems that
relying on her won't solve the problem. Let's find a way to enter the forest in order to
repair the ship. Head north from the location of the road closure. There might be a way to
enter the forest from somewhere.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Scene 15
note:
<SG:The story now shifts to the perspective of Uka-sama. First, it seems she is moving to
repair the broken ship. Let's gather the necessary material, the Flaarus Fruit. It
should be in the western Raulus Forest. Leave the town and head south, then take the fork
in the road to the west.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3-14
note:
<SG:Hmmm, it seems like a dangerous situation. This is bad, we should deal with it
immediately! It doesn't seem like a problem that can be easily solved. Let's head to Shia-
sama, who seems to be feeling cold for now.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Scene 13
note:
<SG:Is this a shipwreck? Thank goodness we're alive. Let's head towards the temple as
instructed by Lady Prae. It's located on the north side of the coast, in the center of the
island. Without paying attention to anything else, let's make our way to the temple.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Scene 12
note:
<SG:The monsters seem to have settled down for now. Shall we talk to the people on the ship?
Please be aware that talking to Lady Shia will advance the conversation.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3-11
note:
<SG:It seems like the negotiation with the captain was successful. Let's go to the harbor in
the north where the captain is. If you're worried about a battle, it's okay to train a
little outside the town before going. Seduction has been used since ancient times. Similar
words like pillow business are often used in a negative sense, but I don't think
seduction is a bad thing. It's just using your own weapon to achieve your goal. It's just
getting close using your body, similar to getting close at a drinking party, isn't it?>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Level 10
note:
<SG:Good morning, you were cuddling with someone last night, weren't you? Sleeping with Uka-
sama instead of your lover? It's fine either way. Well, since there's nothing else to do,
let's try to please the client. I wonder if Shia-sama is on the first floor of the inn?>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Verse 9
note:
<SG:It's nighttime. It seems like there are a lot of things to think about and you're tired.
Let's head to the harbor for a change of mood. Maybe someone will be there.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Section 8
note:
<SG:I see, it's the prelude to a seduction... This is where Nonna-sama's skills will shine.
Well then, let's return to the inn and rest for today. If you talk to the innkeeper, you
can take a break.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Verse 7
note:
<SG:It seems that Shia-sama has already made up her mind about the plan. Let's head to the
harbor and negotiate with the captain.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3-6
note:
<SG:It seems difficult to rent a boat. Let's return to the inn where Shia-sama is. Fighting on
land and fighting at sea are different, you know. Dealing with sea monsters seems quite
challenging.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Section 5
note:
<SG:We heard about the request from 'The Azure Songstress', didn't we? It's a shame that
Taro-sama couldn't enjoy it. Let's head north towards the town. There is a harbor there.
We should negotiate to rent a boat at the harbor. Let's find someone who seems to have a
boat.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3, Section 4
note:
<SG:We've arrived in Rimuru, good job. I don't care about anything that happened along the
way. First, let's go to the inn. We can meet with the Azure Songstress, our client,
there. She's right inside the inn.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3-3
note:
<SG:Last night was enjoyable for everyone, wasn't it? Taro-sama was just sleeping next to Uka-
sama. Let's head to Rimurun in the west. It's not too far away. If we don't make any
detours, we should arrive soon.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3-2
note:
<SG:We've arrived at the inn for now. Let's rest here before heading to the west to Rimurun.
It seems like Nonna-sama has something to discuss. Once we're done with any other
important matters, let's talk to Nonna-sama.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 3-1
note:
<SG:Chapter 3 is about to begin. Let's head to the western Ardea Highway to meet the client.
We'll stay at an inn along the way and continue forward. The client is known as the Azure
Songstress and is a very famous person. She is recognized as one of the top singers on
the continent. However, it seems that she is upset with someone who is a very beautiful
woman... Well, I shouldn't say anymore. I'll restrain myself.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Intermission 2-3
note:
<SG:Yes, it's intermission time. I will give the same explanation as before. Let's complete
dispatch quests to increase our fame. When our fame is high enough, we will be able to
receive main quests from the receptionist. Accepting a main quest will start the next
chapter. Is this clear so far? The pleasure city of Solte has a nature similar to that of
an autonomous city. It pays very little tax to the country, but as a result, it also
receives little assistance. That's why there are many mercenaries and adventurers in this
town. The role of mercenaries and adventurers is to defeat the surrounding monsters, while
the city soldiers are responsible for maintaining public order in the city.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Intermission 2-2
note:
<SG:  Haa... What kind of outfit are you wearing? I can understand why she would be angry, so
please reflect on it. From here on, we will be controlling a different person. There
aren't any formidable enemies, so even if we lose, there won't be any consequences. Let's
keep moving forward.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Intermission 2-1
note:
<SG:Yes, yes, no comment from me. Even though it's called an intermission, I can't move
freely. If you're looking for Princess Prae, it might be a good idea to go outside.
Although it would be troublesome if you walked around with that crotch...>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2, Scene 16
note:
<SG:Thank you for your hard work in defeating the monsters. Let's report to my beloved lover,
Kuno-sama. She is probably in her own room. Kuno-sama's room is the second one from the
right, on the top.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2, Scene 15
note:
<SG:There was an underground cave, right? Going underground in a swamp, it's like a fantasy.
It seems that the target monster is somewhere below, so let's go down. And once we find
the target monster...>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2, Scene 14
note:
<SG:It was such a pleasure to meet you. How many times do I have to say it to satisfy you? It
seems we have arrived near our destination. It's called the Agart Wetlands, right? It
took a long time just to get here. We don't know where the monsters are, so let's explore.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2, Scene 13
note:
<SG:Since morning has come, let's depart. You can leave by talking to the coachman. What
happened over there last night? Well, I'm in a different place, so I don't know, you know?>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2, Verse 12
note:
<SG:It seems we've passed through the Akeru Wilderness. Let's set up camp first before moving
forward. It looks like everyone is taking a break as they please. Since I have some
business to attend to, let's talk to Lady Fross.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2-11
note:
<SG:Let's go through the Akeru Wilderness. If we head northeast, we should be able to get
through. If the enemies are too strong and it's tough, I think it's okay to level up and
earn money to become stronger before moving forward.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2-10
note:
<SG:Well, it's time to embark on a journey. The non-combat parts were quite long, weren't
they? Let's head to the Akel Wilderness. It's located northeast of the town. By the way,
if you're not confident in your strength, you might want to level up in other places.
Equipment strength is important, so don't forget to prepare your equipment.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2, Section 9
note:
<SG:Last night was enjoyable, wasn't it? How many times is this now? I hope this will be the
last enjoyment before we go out. First, let's meet the coachman. The coachman is near the
entrance of the town.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2, Section 8
note:
<SG:Beautiful women are truly reliable. However, she really hates doing that task, so please
don't push her too hard. It seems she felt nauseous as soon as we went underground. Now
that we finally know how to deal with it, all that's left is to defeat the monsters. Let's
go back and rest for today.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>//

name: Chapter 2, Verse 7
note:
<SG:Last night was enjoyable, wasn't it? I'm glad you're doing well. For now, let's head
towards the direction with the kitchen. If there's a stunning beauty there, feel free to
strike up a conversation.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2-6
note:
<SG:Last night was enjoyable, wasn't it? It's a common sight for a prostitution mercenary
group like us. Fross-sama managed to escape, so let's go meet Prae-sama. She's probably in
her own room on the 2nd floor now.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2, Section 5
note:
<SG:I see, so that's what happened. Kuno-sama, involved in such a thing... It's a relief that
it happened when I wasn't around. Let's bring Fross-sama into the room and have a talk. I
know what we're going to talk about.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2-4
note:
<SG:It's unfortunate that things have become complicated even though I went through the
trouble of helping. In order to treat the symptoms, it's best that the two lovers... do it
when I'm not around. I don't want to hear about it, after all. Let's go back to the base.
They should be there.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2-3
note:
<SG:Thank you for your efforts in searching for the missing person. I'm glad they were found
safe and sound. Let's take a rest in the room after taking a bath. Since you're tired,
it's best not to go outside. However, I would be troubled if I were treated to an
unappetizing meal. It's difficult to judge whether it's out of goodwill or ill intent.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2-2
note:
<SG:We have arrived at Mount Kapel. Let's search for the missing person by climbing up here.
However, it's also important to turn back if it feels too difficult. Let's prepare our
equipment and recovery items.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2-1
note:
<SG:Chapter 2 begins. Let's head to Mount Capel and search for the missing person. The
location is to the south of town. Let's make sure to prepare our equipment properly before
heading there. By the way, equipment is very important. If we don't prepare properly, we
might end up in a painful situation, so let's be careful.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Intermission 1
note:
<SG:The receptionist is a very beautiful person, isn't she? Everyone must admire someone like
her. Now, it's time for the intermission. Let's complete dispatch quests to increase our
fame. As your fame rises, you'll be able to receive main quests from the receptionist.
Accepting main quests will start the next chapter. By the way, this town is known as a
pleasure city. It's a place where mercenaries and adventurers often gather, and it's an
area with a high occurrence of monsters.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 1-6
note:
<SG:You did your best today as well. Now all that's left is to sleep... but it seems that
Kuno-sama is outside. Let's have a little chat before going to bed.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 1-5
note:
<SG:We have arrived at the Prop Forest. If the situation worsens, let's return to town and
regroup. Let's proceed deeper to find the desired explosive laughing mushroom. Anyone who
gets in our way will be... cough cough, nothing at all.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 1-4
note:
<SG:Last night was enjoyable, wasn't it? What? You didn't enjoy it? I see. This time it's
work. We're going to gather materials for the menu at the adult entertainment
establishment. Let's head to the Prope Forest near town. By the way, the reason the
mercenary group's location is at the edge is because they also run an adult entertainment
establishment and the sound of their training is noisy.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 1-3
note:
<SG:Hmm... I think the story is quite long, isn't it? I'd like to summarize it in three
lines... Well then. Three people were on the verge of death, but they were saved by making
a contract with Lady Prae. It seems that the three of them have become succubi with NTR
tendencies due to Taro-sama's nature as the contracted party. By the way, they also became
the leader of a mercenary group and the manager of a brothel. It doesn't feel very
cohesive, does it? Shall we just go to bed quietly today?>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 1-2
note:
<SG:Your parents have passed away, haven't they? By the way, is that person the culprit? It's
the No.IX of the Aegis in the Misura Kingdom, right? It's famous for single-handedly
annihilating the Dios Kingdom army. Let's descend from the cliff to the east and head
north. It seems like you're getting fired up because it's your enemy.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 1
note:
<SG:Thank you for defeating the thieves. It's great that the woman who was captured has become
our ally. Now, let's head north for the next adventure. Don't worry about our equipment
being the same as before. I'm excited to hear what happened on the day you met Lady Prae.
But you were lovers, and even got married with three people. You're quite popular, huh?
Hyu-hyu (robotic voice).>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 2
note:
<SG:It seems we have arrived at the thief's cave. There are thieves based here, let's defeat
their leader. By the way, even if we lose now, there will be no consequences. Let's tear
them apart and throw them away.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //

name: Chapter 1
note:
<SG:Nice to meet you, everyone. For those who are already familiar, it's been a while. I will
be in charge of the summary. Please take care of me. Now, you are heading towards the
eradication of thieves. First, let's go north and head to the thieves' cave.>           // (1)
<SG:>// 
<SG>            //
